From: Liu Gang <Gang.Liu@freescale.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2015 15:36:52 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 190/214] LS2080A/GPIO: Modify out_be32 to iowrite32be

GPIO controller's registers are big endian, the
accessors ioread32be/iowrite32be matches this one
and portable on powerpc as well on ARM.

Signed-off-by: Liu Gang <Gang.Liu@freescale.com>
Change-Id: I09869cd6c2af8ca23643aa73b8bb0b6a6e593907
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/35674
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Stuart Yoder <stuart.yoder@freescale.com>
[Original patch extracted from FSL LS2085 SDK EAR5.0,
Layerscape2-SDK-SOURCE-20150828-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Jiang Lu <lu.jiang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpio/gpio-mpc8xxx.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpio/gpio-mpc8xxx.c b/drivers/gpio/gpio-mpc8xxx.c
index be4954a..9bc8506 100644
--- a/drivers/gpio/gpio-mpc8xxx.c
+++ b/drivers/gpio/gpio-mpc8xxx.c
@@ -137,7 +137,7 @@ static void mpc8xxx_gpio_set_multiple(struct gpio_chip *gc,
 		}
 	}
 
-	out_be32(mm->regs + GPIO_DAT, mpc8xxx_gc->data);
+	iowrite32be(mpc8xxx_gc->data, mm->regs + GPIO_DAT);
 
 	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&mpc8xxx_gc->lock, flags);
 }
